{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"056ef14e-85c8-4076-bb51-5e66ad36d95e","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API with OpenAPI support (default in .NET 8+)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"edd2713a-523b-4b90-afd2-a1c8a407cf8d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET development question. Let me check if there's relevant content in this repository that might help answer this, particularly in the plugins directory.\n\nActually, looking at the context - this is a general knowledge question about creating a web API project with authentication. I don't need to search the codebase for this - it's a standard .NET/development question I can answer from knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":386,"requestId":"5001:1E3C:274A5C0:2B29375:69FBE235"},"id":"0bde011f-1939-4eb2-a766-24a083bb323a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:52:15.114Z","parentId":"edc1451f-87f2-4d5b-aa5d-9b27c61db607"}
